text: Philip Wells Woods (November 2, 1931 - September 29, 2015) was an American jazz bebop alto saxophonist, clarinetist, bandleader and composer. Woods was born in Springfield, Massachusetts. Woods died from emphysema on September 29, 2015 in East Stroudsburg, Pennsylvania. He was 83. ==References== * Gonzalez, Henry (1990). The Armadillo Years: A Visual History * Nisenson, Eric (1996). Round About Midnight -- A Portrait of Miles Davis (2nd ed.).
